<h2 class="nounderline">Grants Coordinator and Development Associate</h2>

<p><strong>POSITION:</strong><span class="nounderline"> Grants Coordinator and Development Associate</span><br />
  <strong>SUPERVISOR: </strong>Debbie Andrews<br />
  <strong>STATUS:</strong> Full-time, Exempt</p>
<p><strong>RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong><br />
  <strong>Grants and Fundraising</strong></p>
<ol start="1" type="1">
  <li>Conduct grant research and write grants for PACER&rsquo;s local and national projects.</li>
  <li>Make contacts with prospective donors, including for the Endowment Fund.</li>
  <li>Track, monitor, contact, and acknowledge individuals in the donor base.</li>
  <li>Coordinate, research, and draft      proposals for funding.</li>
  <li>Draft letters and other materials      for PACER.</li>
  <li>Make contacts with new corporations and foundations, local and national.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Special Events</strong></p>
<ol>
  <li>Assist with event logistics for PACER&rsquo;s various events, including the Run, Walk, Roll Against Bullying, Annual Benefit, and Phonathon.</li>
  <li>Solicit new corporate sponsors and in-kind donations.</li>
  <li>Recruit and schedule volunteers.</li>
  <li>Provide staff support, as needed, with committees and advisory boards, including the Young Professionals Advisory Board.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Special Projects</strong></p>
<ol start="1" type="1">
  <li>Develop      content and provide updates for development web pages.</li>
  <li>Coordinate      social media communications for development related events and activities.</li>
  <li>Assist with project data collection and evaluation.</li>
  <li>Other      duties as needed.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>REQUIREMENTS:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>College degree required</li>
  <li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills</li>
  <li>Experience in event planning and marketing</li>
  <li>Ability to use discretion and diplomacy when communicating with donors and sponsors</li>
  <li>Excellent organizational skills, ability to prioritize, and meet deadlines</li>
  <li>Knowledge and sensitivity to issues, current information, and research related to persons with disabilities</li>
  <li>Accuracy and attention to detail</li>
  <li>Ability to manage multiple tasks on several projects</li>
  <li>Ability to collaborate with co-workers and coordinate projects</li>
  <li>Ability to work independently and participate in team planning and decision-making process</li>
  <li>Above average proficiency of computer software programs; primarily Microsoft Office with an emphasis on Word, Excel and PowerPoint</li>
  <li>Ability to develop positive relationships with community members, donors, volunteers, and staff</li>
</ul>
<p>Position available immediately. Parents of children with disabilities are encouraged to apply. Salary to be determined based on experience. </p>
